WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.633
(birds chirping)

00:08.633 --> 00:10.844
(wind blowing)

00:10.844 --> 00:14.055
(Barry gasping)

00:15.223 --> 00:18.935
Barry:
<i>Lord, please watch over me</i>

00:18.935 --> 00:22.272
<i>and fill me with
your courage and grace.</i>

00:22.272 --> 00:25.692
(voice breaking)
<i>Please watch over my son John</i>

00:25.692 --> 00:28.528
<i>and fill his heart
with his daddy's love.</i>

00:28.528 --> 00:30.822
Jim:
<i>So you're a man
of God now?</i>

00:30.822 --> 00:33.783
Barry:
<i>Please take away
all his nightmares.</i>

00:33.783 --> 00:36.286
Jim: <i>You think
because you've repented,</i>

00:36.286 --> 00:39.247
<i>you get to choose
where you're gonna go
after you die?</i>

00:39.247 --> 00:41.791
Barry:
<i>Give his mother the strength
to look over him.</i>

00:41.791 --> 00:44.753
Jim:
<i>You know where you're goin',
and you're afraid.</i>

00:44.753 --> 00:46.588
Barry (whimpering):
<i>I just want my boy
to be safe.</i>

00:46.588 --> 00:50.550
- (wind blowing,
waves washing ashore)
- (Barry gasping)

00:50.550 --> 00:52.510
Barry:
<i>Why are you
showing me this?</i>

00:52.510 --> 00:55.597
Jim:
<i>I'm not showin' you anything.</i>

00:55.597 --> 00:57.891
<i>This is all in
your head, Barry.</i>

00:59.559 --> 01:02.145
Barry:
<i>Why can't I feel
my arms and legs?</i>

01:02.145 --> 01:03.813
Jim:
<i>I cut them off.</i>

01:03.813 --> 01:06.065
(Barry crying)

01:06.065 --> 01:07.776
Barry:
<i>Please...</i>

01:07.776 --> 01:11.446
Jim:
<i>I wanna watch you experience
seeing the people you love</i>

01:11.446 --> 01:13.281
<i>- for the last time.</i>
- (Barry crying)

01:13.281 --> 01:16.326
(deep, menacing music)

01:16.326 --> 01:18.328
Barry:
<i>John...</i>

01:18.328 --> 01:20.163
<i>Oh, my God.</i> (sobs)

01:20.163 --> 01:21.956
<i>Oh, my God, John.</i>

01:21.956 --> 01:25.043
- (whimpering)
- (deep, menacing tone)

01:25.043 --> 01:27.796
- (sobbing)
- (cacophony swells)

01:27.796 --> 01:30.423
- (gasps)
- (silence)

01:30.423 --> 01:34.219
- (whimpering)
- (chair creaking)

01:35.553 --> 01:37.764
(birds chirping outside)

01:37.764 --> 01:40.141
(car passing)

01:40.433 --> 01:42.852
Tom:
"The world needs to know
what the studio is doing

01:42.852 --> 01:44.562
"by making this movie.

01:44.562 --> 01:47.190
"They are
sensationalizing a tragedy

01:47.190 --> 01:50.944
and elevating a murderer.
I will not let that happen."

01:52.654 --> 01:54.197
There's all these comments.

01:54.197 --> 01:55.824
Look at that,
they're all positive.

01:55.824 --> 01:58.576
- Gene: See? It's working.
- Tom: Yeah. You know,

01:58.576 --> 02:01.579
this is like a really
interesting way to go, Gene.

02:01.579 --> 02:02.831
Really.

02:02.831 --> 02:05.208
I mean, I didn't think of
it before, but it's like--

02:05.208 --> 02:07.001
it's like y-you're decided

02:07.001 --> 02:09.045
to take th-the more
honorable path, you know?

02:09.045 --> 02:11.923
Hey, all I'm trying to do
is protect her memory.

02:12.423 --> 02:14.008
I'll tell you what
you're doing with this.

02:14.008 --> 02:16.052
You are showing them
to be the whores
that they are!

02:16.052 --> 02:17.512
That's what you're doing!

02:18.054 --> 02:20.014
Yeah.

02:20.014 --> 02:23.017
♪ ♪

02:23.017 --> 02:26.229
(quiet lobby chatter)

02:27.272 --> 02:30.108
(somber music)

02:33.403 --> 02:35.155
Val:
They're waiting for you.

02:37.115 --> 02:38.199
Who?

02:38.199 --> 02:40.994
The men that we're going
to send to kill Fuches.

02:42.370 --> 02:44.706
The Four Ultimate
Badass Killers?

02:44.706 --> 02:46.916
FUBKs. Yes.

02:47.792 --> 02:49.085
Wait, those guys are real?

02:49.085 --> 02:51.254
- Val: Francisco Boya.
- NoHo Hank: Wow

02:51.254 --> 02:52.589
Val:
Weapons expert.

02:52.589 --> 02:54.007
Used to run missions
for the Clateen cartel.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.884
- NoHo Hank: This is nice.
- Val: Prefers to use a knife

02:55.884 --> 02:57.927
because he likes to be
close to his victims.

02:57.927 --> 03:00.013
NoHo Hank:
Yes. Sold. Add to cart.

03:00.013 --> 03:02.390
Val:
Konstantine Persky. Explosions.

03:02.390 --> 03:05.435
NoHo Hank:
Feel free to blow up cars.
Fuches, obviously. Right?

03:05.435 --> 03:08.271
That'd be hilarious.
Fuches with dynamite
tied to him.

03:08.271 --> 03:11.232
- Val: Like the Wile E. Coyote!
- NoHo Hank: Exactly. Next.

03:11.232 --> 03:13.693
Val:
Todd Geer,
ex-Special Forces.

03:13.693 --> 03:15.570
Responsible for
leading six coups.

03:15.570 --> 03:18.448
- More like four and a half.
- NoHo Hank: Hey, don't downplay
your accomplishments.

03:18.448 --> 03:20.533
That's still a shitload
of coups, Todd.

03:20.909 --> 03:23.244
- Uh, yes, please.
- Val: Isiah Ransone.

03:23.244 --> 03:25.163
- NoHo Hank: Oh, he can get it.
- Val: Sharpshooter.

03:25.163 --> 03:27.916
- NoHo Hank: Of course he is.
- Val: 500 confirmed kills.

03:27.916 --> 03:29.709
NoHo Hank:
Make that 501.

03:30.209 --> 03:32.503
Okay, so when can we expect
this job to be done?

03:32.503 --> 03:33.796
Val:
EOD.

03:33.796 --> 03:35.340
And what does that mean?

03:35.340 --> 03:38.384
- Val: End of the day.
- Okay, then just say
"end of day," alright?

03:38.384 --> 03:41.471
You're not Special Forces
like Isiah Ransone over here.

03:42.513 --> 03:43.848
Now, go.

03:44.641 --> 03:46.225
Wipe them out.

03:46.225 --> 03:48.436
Leave no witnesses.

03:48.436 --> 03:51.689
And before you kill
Fuches, tell him...

03:52.732 --> 03:54.859
"NoHo Hank did this."

03:57.695 --> 03:59.656
- Oh God.
- (car passing)

03:59.656 --> 04:01.366
John.

04:01.950 --> 04:03.201
<i>John...</i>

04:03.201 --> 04:06.746
<i>John, I don't want this to
be the last time I see you.</i>

04:07.747 --> 04:09.207
John.

04:09.874 --> 04:12.126
(soft crying)

04:12.126 --> 04:14.087
I love you so much.

04:14.754 --> 04:17.840
- Please say something to me.
- (chair rattling)

04:17.840 --> 04:20.802
John, please say something.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.013
John,
please say something to me.

04:24.013 --> 04:27.183
- (slams hammer)
- Daddy loves you so much, John.

04:27.183 --> 04:29.394
(pliers rattling)

04:29.394 --> 04:32.730
- Oh shit...
- (snips, slams)

04:33.398 --> 04:35.066
- Oh.
- (Jim sighs)

04:35.066 --> 04:37.652
Oh my... Mr. Cousineau.

04:37.652 --> 04:40.238
(chair rattling)

04:40.238 --> 04:41.948
Mr. Cousineau!

04:43.241 --> 04:45.326
- (chair rattling)
- Mr. Cousineau!

04:45.326 --> 04:47.745
- (inaudible)
<i>- Mr. Cousineau!</i>

04:47.745 --> 04:50.248
<i>I'm so sorry!</i>

04:50.707 --> 04:53.084
Mr. Cousineau, I'm so sorry!

04:53.084 --> 04:56.629
<i>I'm so sorry that happened!
I tried to fix things!</i>

04:57.588 --> 05:00.883
Honestly, I tried to fix things!
I tried to give you that money!

05:00.883 --> 05:03.428
$250,000!

05:03.428 --> 05:05.805
- (whimpers)
- $250,000?

05:08.307 --> 05:10.560
I was trying to fix things.

05:11.769 --> 05:14.605
$250,000?

05:14.605 --> 05:17.817
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

05:19.152 --> 05:21.279
F-For who, Barry?

05:21.279 --> 05:23.531
Mr. Cousineau,

05:24.449 --> 05:26.492
I'm so sorry.

05:26.492 --> 05:28.828
(crying)
I'm so sorry...

05:29.287 --> 05:31.247
- (chair rattles)
- (drops knife)

05:31.247 --> 05:34.459
(dramatic music)

05:38.880 --> 05:41.424
(Barry whimpers)
Please turn this off!

05:45.136 --> 05:46.721
Turn it off!

05:49.098 --> 05:52.435
I'm sorry! I'm sorry...

05:52.435 --> 05:54.479
(music swells)

05:54.479 --> 05:56.647
(dramatic music fades out)

05:57.982 --> 06:01.110
(phone buzzing)

06:02.987 --> 06:05.573
(buzzing stops)

06:05.573 --> 06:07.867
- Gene Cousineau.
- Matt Iserson (on phone):
<i>Mr. Cousineau,</i>

06:07.867 --> 06:09.535
<i>I'm so happy
I got a hold of you.</i>

06:09.535 --> 06:12.955
<i>My name is Matt Iserson.
I'm an agent at UTA.</i>

06:12.955 --> 06:14.248
Oh, you're the guy
that's gonna help me

06:14.248 --> 06:16.959
take out an ad in
"The Hollywood Reporter"

06:16.959 --> 06:18.711
about Warner Brothers
being such a dickhead

06:18.711 --> 06:21.964
'cause they're trying
to profit off the murder
of my girlfriend.

06:22.507 --> 06:25.593
Matt:
<i>No. Actually, I-I'm calling
on behalf of a client.</i>

06:25.593 --> 06:27.678
<i>He wants to play you
in that movie.</i>

06:27.678 --> 06:30.098
Hey. Not interested.

06:30.098 --> 06:32.892
Matt:
<i>My client is
Daniel Day-Lewis.</i>

06:34.519 --> 06:36.604
From "My Left Foot"?

06:36.604 --> 06:39.023
Matt:
<i>Wow, that's a deep cut,
but yes.</i>

06:39.023 --> 06:40.858
<i>Oscar-winner
Daniel Day-Lewis.</i>

06:40.858 --> 06:43.736
<i>He'd like to come out
of retirement to play you.</i>

06:45.780 --> 06:48.324
This is not Tony Danza
trying to fuck with me,
is it?

06:48.324 --> 06:51.828
Matt:
<i>I am not Tony Danza.
My name is Matt Iserson.</i>

06:51.828 --> 06:53.121
<i>I'm an agent at UTA,</i>

06:53.121 --> 06:55.498
<i>and I'd love to fill you in
on the details.</i>

06:55.498 --> 06:57.208
<i>A-Are you open to that?</i>

06:58.000 --> 07:01.170
(nervously rubbing leg)

07:01.170 --> 07:03.381
(deep exhale)

07:03.840 --> 07:06.300
- I guess I'm free today.
- Matt: <i>Great.</i>

07:06.300 --> 07:09.679
<i>- How about
Toscana in an hour?</i>
- Toscana, no.

07:09.679 --> 07:11.889
I'll text you the location.

07:13.057 --> 07:14.725
- (slaps phone)
- (sighs)

07:16.185 --> 07:18.729
(phone buzzing)

07:19.647 --> 07:21.315
- Yes?
- Sally (on phone):
<i>Mr. Cousineau?</i>

07:21.315 --> 07:22.900
(traffic noise over phone)

07:22.900 --> 07:25.528
<i>- Mr. Cousineau,
are you there?</i>
- Sally?

07:25.528 --> 07:27.655
(traffic noise continues)

07:27.655 --> 07:30.825
- Sally: <i>You're alive?</i>
- Uh, yeah.

07:30.825 --> 07:32.535
Sally:
<i>Oh, thank God.</i>

07:32.535 --> 07:34.245
So are you.

07:34.245 --> 07:37.415
Sally:
<i>Okay, uh, listen, I...</i>

07:37.415 --> 07:39.417
<i>I need your help.</i>

07:39.417 --> 07:42.628
Anything, sweetheart.
But wh-where are you?

07:42.628 --> 07:45.423
I'm in Los Angeles
with my son.

07:46.549 --> 07:49.177
John! Stay close to me!

07:50.011 --> 07:52.805
Yeah. Um, listen, um...

07:52.805 --> 07:56.559
We're at the airport.
Um, can you come pick us up?

07:56.559 --> 07:58.895
(traffic noise continues)

07:58.895 --> 08:02.148
- Now?
- Sally: <i>Yeah.
It would be a huge help.</i>

08:03.900 --> 08:06.110
Yeah, no.
No, I-I have to go to Tosca--

08:06.110 --> 08:09.447
I-I have a--
I have a meeting,
I just can't miss it.

08:09.447 --> 08:11.032
Can't you reschedule?

08:11.032 --> 08:13.034
(traffic noise continues)

08:13.034 --> 08:14.952
I'll tell you what.

08:14.952 --> 08:17.163
Go to my house,
and we'll meet there later.

08:17.163 --> 08:19.707
Yeah. Okay. Okay.

08:19.707 --> 08:22.418
- Do you remember the address?
- Sally: <i>Yeah, I remember.</i>

08:22.418 --> 08:24.503
- Okay.
- Sally: <i>Okay,
I'll see you soon.</i>

08:24.503 --> 08:26.297
- (call disconnected tone)
- (sighs)

08:30.551 --> 08:31.761
(panting) Okay.

08:31.761 --> 08:34.263
Look, we need to find a way
to get to Cousineau's.

08:34.263 --> 08:35.473
He's an old friend of mine.

08:35.473 --> 08:37.516
We're gonna meet
your daddy there, okay?

08:37.516 --> 08:39.352
- And once we find him...
- (plane approaching)

08:39.352 --> 08:41.854
- ...everything's gonna
be okay. Okay?
- (plane roaring)

08:41.854 --> 08:44.941
Come on. Come on, come on!

08:44.941 --> 08:48.694
(plane fading)

08:49.320 --> 08:51.697
I got your text!

08:51.697 --> 08:53.241
What's the word
on the FUBKs?

08:53.241 --> 08:55.785
They landed
about an hour ago.

08:55.785 --> 08:57.745
We lost communication
with them.

08:59.163 --> 09:01.415
Okay...

09:01.415 --> 09:03.626
Can you find communication?

09:03.626 --> 09:04.627
Val:
We, uh,

09:04.627 --> 09:07.630
we just got a delivery.
From Fuches.

09:18.099 --> 09:20.851
- It's their heads.
- We don't know that yet.

09:21.227 --> 09:24.855
(cardboard rustling)

09:26.524 --> 09:27.733
It's a head.

09:28.442 --> 09:30.611
I can, uh, find
a couple more FUBKs.

09:30.611 --> 09:33.864
FUBKs don't just grow out of
the ground like mint, okay?

09:33.864 --> 09:35.950
(sighs) It's another head.

09:35.950 --> 09:38.411
I will go alone and, uh,

09:38.411 --> 09:39.870
avenge the FUBKs for--

09:39.870 --> 09:42.373
Oh, yeah? You're gonna go
on a suicide mission, Val, huh?

09:42.373 --> 09:45.167
Listen, I need you, okay?
You're my support system.

09:45.167 --> 09:47.962
- Why am I still opening these?
- (sighs) Thank God.

09:47.962 --> 09:50.965
- (cardboard rustling)
- Ah, Isiah!

09:51.841 --> 09:54.468
Fuck. Even in death,

09:54.468 --> 09:56.470
just an absolute fox.

09:56.804 --> 09:58.306
Accomplice:
Can I make a suggestion?

09:58.306 --> 10:00.516
I think getting the monsters
out of the house

10:00.516 --> 10:02.435
is more important
than the house.

10:03.769 --> 10:07.440
You know what?
You're absolutely
fucking right.

10:07.440 --> 10:10.359
Fuck that house.
It is dead to us.

10:10.359 --> 10:12.653
Let's take care
of this shit ourselves.

10:14.613 --> 10:16.157
Let's ride.

10:16.157 --> 10:19.327
(mop squishing)

10:20.953 --> 10:24.165
Fuches:
I understand what you guys
witnessed earlier today

10:24.165 --> 10:27.668
was upsetting.
That true?

10:28.836 --> 10:30.963
What about it upsets you?

10:32.840 --> 10:35.217
You cutting off their heads.

10:35.217 --> 10:37.094
I see. Well...

10:38.179 --> 10:40.389
The Raven's flock
are blood artists.

10:40.389 --> 10:42.558
We are modern-day
barbarians.

10:42.558 --> 10:45.895
Our clay
are the beating hearts
of our enemy.

10:45.895 --> 10:48.522
No, yeah, you've told us
this a number of times.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.067
Right, right,
but me saying it

10:51.067 --> 10:52.568
and you saying it,
two different things.

10:52.568 --> 10:54.195
- That's right.
- Fuches: Yeah.

10:54.195 --> 10:55.529
(inhales)

10:55.529 --> 10:57.198
Shit. Okay.

10:57.907 --> 11:00.618
Well, should've thought
this out more.

11:01.285 --> 11:02.370
(sucks teeth)

11:03.245 --> 11:05.539
- May I make a suggestion?
- Fuches: Mm-hmm.

11:05.539 --> 11:06.874
Next time we
capture enemies,

11:06.874 --> 11:09.835
I or one of the guys
take the ladies
out for a meal,

11:09.835 --> 11:12.338
so they're not here
when shit goes down.

11:12.338 --> 11:15.341
Nice. It's a nice idea.
Delightful meal.

11:15.591 --> 11:19.011
And when you come back,
it's all cleaned up.

11:19.011 --> 11:21.347
Yo, that was, like,
a sneak attack, though.

11:21.347 --> 11:22.973
I-I'm not trying
to be all whatever,

11:22.973 --> 11:25.643
- but can't really, like,
plan for those.
- Right. I get it. Right, right.

11:25.643 --> 11:27.478
(clicks tongue)
Yo, what about, uh,

11:27.478 --> 11:29.605
like, noise-canceling
headphones?

11:29.605 --> 11:31.273
(Fuches sighs)

11:32.566 --> 11:34.693
You could put on a movie.

11:35.486 --> 11:37.697
But those guys were
screaming really loud.

11:38.406 --> 11:41.075
You could just
put the volume up.

11:41.075 --> 11:43.869
If it's a
"Fast and Furious,"
you won't hear shit.

11:44.703 --> 11:47.832
That's not gonna
drown out dudes gettin'
their heads cut off.

11:47.832 --> 11:50.042
The one with the planes
on the runway.

11:50.042 --> 11:53.003
I saw it in the theaters,
and my ears
are ringing for days.

11:53.003 --> 11:55.297
What, was that "Tokyo Drift"?
Is that the one
with Lil' Bow Wow?

11:55.297 --> 11:57.383
No, it's "Furious 6."
Uh, came out, like, 2013.

11:57.383 --> 11:58.676
- Six? I didn't see Six.
- That's the one

11:58.676 --> 12:00.469
where Toretto comes out
the front of the plane--

12:00.469 --> 12:02.847
It doesn't matter.
They're all loud.

12:02.847 --> 12:05.099
You gotta have a legit soundbar
if you want that to work, dude.

12:05.099 --> 12:07.351
Soundbar or no soundbar,
the movie is loud.

12:07.351 --> 12:10.646
Okay, <i>muchacho...</i>
(speaking Spanish)

12:10.646 --> 12:14.233
..."Fast <i>y</i> Furious"...
(continues in Spanish)

12:14.233 --> 12:16.444
Okay?
(speaking Spanish)

12:21.365 --> 12:24.076
I still think
I can time it
where we get them

12:24.076 --> 12:27.455
out of the house
for a nice meal
before shit goes down.

12:27.455 --> 12:30.750
- (birds chirping)
- (stream flowing)

12:46.599 --> 12:49.143
Gene Cousineau?
Matt Iserson.

12:49.143 --> 12:51.353
Pretend you don't know me.

12:53.522 --> 12:54.607
Um...

12:55.983 --> 12:57.193
Uh-- (clears throat)

12:57.193 --> 12:59.361
Daniel hasn't been this
excited about a role in ages--

12:59.361 --> 13:01.947
Act like you're talking
on your phone.

13:02.656 --> 13:03.741
(sighs)

13:05.493 --> 13:06.577
(sighs)

13:09.538 --> 13:13.292
Daniel really
loved the complexity
of your character.

13:13.292 --> 13:16.712
The, uh, pathos, the courage,
the huge personality.

13:16.712 --> 13:18.088
I-It's the total package.

13:18.088 --> 13:20.674
But, i-in today's landscape, unfortunately,

13:20.674 --> 13:22.384
Daniel's not enough.

13:22.384 --> 13:24.512
It's why we need to attach
another big name

13:24.512 --> 13:27.181
- for the role of Berkman.
- Are you telling me

13:27.181 --> 13:29.141
that Daniel can't
get a movie made?

13:29.141 --> 13:32.061
Not a theater movie.
Maybe a phone movie.

13:32.061 --> 13:34.897
But, I think this story is big.

13:34.897 --> 13:37.358
- I-It's not small.
- Yeah, right.

13:37.358 --> 13:40.152
And I have a client
who wants to play Barry.

13:40.986 --> 13:42.363
Mark Wahlberg.

13:42.696 --> 13:44.323
Mark Wahlberg?

13:45.324 --> 13:46.909
Are you shitting me?

13:46.909 --> 13:49.119
Well, we ran this through
our marketing division,

13:49.119 --> 13:50.788
and if we brought Mark on,

13:50.788 --> 13:53.165
the studios would be in
a bidding war tomorrow.

13:53.165 --> 13:54.333
Hm...

13:55.084 --> 13:56.335
Well,

13:56.335 --> 13:58.921
this would be a great way
to get Janice's story out there.

